 
#Awesome & Free Linux Games: 

**Strategy / Tactics:**

* [FreeCiv](http://www.freeciv.org/) - Free clone of Civilization

* [FreeCol](http://www.freecol.org/news/freecol-0.11.6-released.html) - Free clone of Colonization, based in colonial America

* [FreeOrion](http://www.freeorion.org/index.php/Main_Page) - Free Clone of the classic Master of Orion strategy game

* [OpenRA](http://www.openra.net/) - An open-source implementation of Command & Conquer: Red Alert, Tiberian Sun, and Dune 2000, all in one place!

* [Tanks of Freedom](https://w84death.itch.io/tanks-of-freedom) - Turn based strategy game, similar to the Advance Wars games on the GBA.

* [The Battle For Wesnoth](https://www.wesnoth.org/) - Free open-source turn-based fantasy RPG/Strategy hybrid

* [Hedgewars](http://www.hedgewars.org/) - a free clone of the game Worms

* [UFO: Alien Invasion](https://ufoai.org/wiki/News) - A free turn-based tactical combat game, inspired by the X-Com series.

* [Argentum Age](http://www.argentumage.com/) - A free and open-source fantasy card game

* [UFO2000](http://ufo2000.sourceforge.net/) - Another X-com type of game

* [Wyrmsun](https://andrettin.github.io/) - An interesting fantasy RTS

* [0 A.D.](https://play0ad.com/) - A truly impressive fully 3D RTS. **(Not suitable for low-end systems)**

* [Spring RTS](https://springrts.com/) - An RTS game engine that has a few complete games made from it, like Zero-K

* [Warzone 2100](https://wz2100.net/) - A 3D RTS that offers campaign, multi-player, and single-player skirmish modes.

* [Megaglest](https://megaglest.org/) - RTS game where you control the armies of one of seven different factions

**City Builder/Tycoon:**

* [OpenTTD](https://www.openttd.org/en/) - open-source clone based upon Transport Tycoon Deluxe

* [Unknown Horizons](http://unknown-horizons.org/) - Village builder/manager inspired by the Anno series

* [Scorched 3D](http://www.scorched3d.co.uk/) - Simple turn-based artillery game and also a real-time strategy game in which players can counter each othersâ€™ weapons with other creative accessories, shields and tactics.

* [Simutrans](https://www.simutrans.com/en/) -Open-source transportation simulator. Your goal is to establish a successful transport company. 

**Adventure/RPG:**

* [Heroine's Quest](http://crystalshard.net/?g=16) - Fantastic free Point'n'Click RPG inspired by the Quest for Glory series from Sierra

* [Beneath a Steel Sky](https://www.gog.com/game/beneath_a_steel_sky) - Classic adventure game with excellent artwork and voice talent. Should be available in the Ubuntu repos

* [ScummVM's Freeware Games](https://www.scummvm.org/games) - Some fantastic point'n'click games here, my favorite probably being Dreamweb

* [Solarus Games](http://www.solarus-games.org/games/solarus-team/) - Solarus is a game engine for making Zelda-like games, but there are many completed games available on their website, and also [community made games](http://www.solarus-games.org/games/community/)

* [Flare](http://flarerpg.org/) - A surprisngly indepth and polished isometric RPG

* [Eldevin](https://www.eldevin.com/) - F2P Runescape clone with a distinct charm

**Roguelikes:**

* [Dwarf Fortress](http://www.bay12games.com/dwarves/) - The most famous Rogue-like/City-builder around. Extremely daunting to get into, but very rewarding if you do **(Not suitable for low-end systems)**

* [Roguebox Adventures](https://rogueboxadventures.tuxfamily.org/) - Neat little graphical rogue-like with a focus on survival and crafting. [Source code here](https://notabug.org/themightyglider/RogueBoxAdventuresMirror) for packagers

* [Cataclysm: Dark Days Ahead](https://cataclysmdda.org/) - Unique zombie survival rogue-like, very in-depth.

* [UnReal World](http://www.unrealworld.fi/) - Crazy in-depth survival roguelike based in iron age Finland

* [Dungeon Crawl Soup](https://crawl.develz.org/) - A roguelike adventure through dungeons filled with dangerous monsters in a quest to find the mystifyingly fabulous Orb of Zot.

* [NetHack](https://www.nethack.org/) - Does this need an introduction?

* [Brogue](https://sites.google.com/site/broguegame/home) - Another in-depth roguelike with its own appeal

* [Tales of Maj'Eyal: Age of Ascendancy](https://te4.org/) - Ultra polished graphical roguelike with the option to save your game

* [ADOM (Ancient Domains of Mystery)](https://www.adom.de/home/index.html) - Another great roguelike, with a huge world and many ways to play

**Space Sim/Trading/RPG:**

* [Ur-Quan Masters](http://sc2.sourceforge.net/) - Updated version of the classic game Star Control II. Be sure to download the optional Voice Pack! ([Alternative HD version available here](https://sourceforge.net/projects/urquanmastershd/))

* [Endless Sky](https://endless-sky.github.io/) - 2D space trading and combat game similar to the classic Escape Velocity series

* [Oolite](http://www.oolite.org/) - Well done Elite remake, with plentiful mod support.

* [Pioneer](http://pioneerspacesim.net/#&panel1-1) - a remake to the sequel to Elite, Frontier.

* [Vega Strike](http://vegastrike.sourceforge.net/) - Open Source 3D Action-Space-Sim that lets you trade, fight, and explore in a vast universe.

* [Naev](https://store.steampowered.com/app/598530/Naev/) - open-source game about space exploration, trade and combat


**Puzzle:**

* [FloboPuyo](http://www.ios-software.com/flobopuyo-en) - Open-source clone of the PuyoPuyo games. [Source-code](http://www.fovea.cc/files/flobopuyo) for packagers

* [Frozen Bubble](http://www.frozen-bubble.org/home/) - Great open-source clone of the Bubble Bobble games. Should be available in most distro repos

* [Duck Marines](http://tangramgames.dk/games/duckmarines/) - An open-source clone of the game Chu Chu Rocket. [Source code here](https://github.com/SimonLarsen/duckmarines) for distro packagers.

* [Pingus](https://pingus.seul.org/) - A well done Lemmings clone.

* [Portable Puzzle Collection](https://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/%7Esgtatham/puzzles/) - A pack of 39 "old school" games like Sudoku, Same Game, Flood, etc.

**Arcade/Casual:**

* [SSVOpenHexagon](http://vittorioromeo.info/projects.html) - Open-source clone of the Super Hexagon game. [Source code](https://github.com/SuperV1234/SSVOpenHexagon) for packagers

* [LBreakout2](http://lgames.sourceforge.net/LBreakout2/) - One of the best open-source breakout clones around. Should be able to be found in some distro repos

* [Witch Blast](https://dev.solus-project.com/T1335) - An open-source clone of the Binding of Isaac games. [Source code here](https://github.com/Cirrus-Minor/witchblast) for distro packgers.

* [TeeWorlds](https://store.steampowered.com/app/380840/) - A fun multiplayer 2D shooter, should be available in most repos, as well as Steam.

* [OpenTyrian](https://bitbucket.org/opentyrian/opentyrian/wiki/Home) - The famous Tyrian 2000 reimplemented for other systems

* [Kobo Deluxe](http://olofson.net/kobodl/) - Seems to be an 8-way scrolling shooter

**Side-Scroller:**

* [Mr. Rescue](http://tangramgames.dk/games/mrrescue/) - A small game about a fireman rescuing people from a burning building, and putting out fires. [Source code here](https://github.com/SimonLarsen/mrrescue) for people who want to package it for their distro

* [Sienna](http://tangramgames.dk/games/sienna/) - Fun little runner/platformer. Source-code [can be found here](https://github.com/SimonLarsen/sienna) for those who want to package it for their distro. :)

* [Super Tux](http://www.supertux.org/) - A free and open-source Mario clone, and [currently in need of help if it's to stay alive](https://www.reddit.com/r/linux_gaming/comments/8tmc1x/classic_open_source_game_super_tux_seeking_help/)

* [Hurrican](https://www.winterworks.de/project/hurrican/) - side-scrolling shooter inspired by the classic game Turrican. Unfortunately it's a bit forgotten nowadays, and may not be included in many repos. So [you may have to compile it from here](https://sourceforge.net/p/hurrican/code/HEAD/tree/trunk/)

* [Frogatto](https://frogatto.com/) - Very impressive platformer with great music and graphics. Should be available in the Ubuntu repos for free.

**Racing:**

* [SuperTuxCart](https://supertuxkart.net/Main_Page) - Excellent open-source clone of the Mario Cart games **(Not suitable for low-end systems)**

* [Yorg](http://www.ya2.it/pages/download.html#download) - A top-down racer in the Micro Machine's style.

**First Person Shooter/Stealth:**

* [Xonotic](http://www.xonotic.org/) - Arena-style online shooter, inspired by Quake

* [Dystopia](https://store.steampowered.com/app/17580/Dystopia/) - A cyberpunk online FPS, which a wicked cool atmosphere and unique gameplay, such as jacking into cyberspace to deactivate turrets, unlock doors, etc. Not many people play it nowadays, but it's good fun!

* [Urban Terror](https://www.urbanterror.info/home/) - Fast pased online FPS reminiscent of Counter-strike

* [OpenArena](http://openarena.ws/smfnews.php) - Online arena shooter using the id tech engine

* [Team Fortress 2](https://store.steampowered.com/app/440/Team_Fortress_2/) - class-based online shooter **(Not suitable for low-end systems)**

* [The Dark Mod](http://www.thedarkmod.com/) - Fan-made spin-off the the fantastic Thief series, based off the Doom 3 engine. **(Not suitable for low-end systems)**

**Minecraft Clones:**

* [Minetest](https://www.minetest.net/) - Free Minecraft clone. Requires mods to be on-par with the default Minecraft experience. 

* [TrueCraft](https://github.com/SirCmpwn/TrueCraft) - Open-source clean-room implementation of Minecraft 1.7.3
